{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id055e252b-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1565"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1565"},"text":"§ 1565.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Cartage","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The cartage of merchandise entered for warehouse shall be done by—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id055e252c-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1565/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" cartmen appointed and licensed by the Customs Service; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id055e252d-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1565/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" carriers designated under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t19/s1551"},"text":"section 1551 of this title","children":[],"tail":" to carry bonded merchandise;"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n\n"},{"tag":"continuation","attrib":{},"text":"who shall give bond, in a penal sum to be fixed by the Customs Service, for the protection of the Government against any loss of, or damage to, the merchandise while being so carted. The cartage of merchandise designated for examination at the appraiser’s stores and of merchandise taken into custody by the customs officer as unclaimed shall be performed by such persons as may be designated, under contract or otherwise, by the Secretary of the Treasury, and under such regulations for the protection of the owners thereof and of the revenue as the Secretary of the Treasury shall prescribe.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id055e252e-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1930-06-17/ch497"},"text":"June 17, 1930, ch. 497","children":[],"tail":", title IV, § 565, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/46/747"},"text":"46 Stat. 747","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/271/tIII/s301/x"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–271, title III, § 301(x)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1970-06-02"},"text":"June 2, 1970","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/84/290"},"text":"84 Stat. 290","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/182/tVI/s666"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–182, title VI, § 666","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1993-12-08"},"text":"Dec. 8, 1993","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/107/2215"},"text":"107 Stat. 2215","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id055e252f-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id055e2530-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"priorProvisions","id":"id055e2531-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Prior Provisions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Provisions similar to those in this section were contained in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1922-09-21/ch356/tIV/s565"},"text":"act Sept. 21, 1922, ch. 356, title IV, § 565","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/42/979"},"text":"42 Stat. 979","children":[],"tail":". That section was superseded by section 565 of act "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1930-06-17"},"text":"June 17, 1930","children":[],"tail":", comprising this section, and repealed by section 651(a)(1) of the 1930 act."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1874-06-22/ch391/s25"},"text":"Act June 22, 1874, ch. 391, § 25","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/18/191"},"text":"18 Stat. 191","children":[],"tail":", required cartage of merchandise in the custody of the government to be let to the lowest responsible bidder, prior to repeal by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1922-09-21/ch356/tIV/s643"},"text":"act Sept. 21, 1922, ch. 356, title IV, § 643","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/42/989"},"text":"42 Stat. 989","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id055e2532-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1993—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/182"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–182","children":[],"tail":" amended first sentence generally. Prior to amendment, first sentence read as follows: “The cartage of merchandise entered for warehouse shall be done by cartmen to be appointed and licensed by the appropriate customs officer and who shall give a bond in a penal sum to be fixed by such customs officer, for the protection of the Government against any loss of, or damage to, such merchandise while being so carted.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1970—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/271"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–271","children":[],"tail":" substituted references to appropriate customs officer of customs officer for references to collector of customs or collector wherever appearing."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id055e2533-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id055e2534-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1970 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For effective date of amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/271"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–271","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/271/s203"},"text":"section 203 of Pub. L. 91–271","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t19/s1500"},"text":"section 1500 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"transferOfFunctions","id":"id055e2535-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Transfer of Functions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For transfer of functions, personnel, assets, and liabilities of the United States Customs Service of the Department of the Treasury, including functions of the Secretary of the Treasury relating thereto, to the Secretary of Homeland Security, and for treatment of related references, see sections 203(1), 551(d), 552(d), and 557 of Title 6, Domestic Security, and the Department of Homeland Security Reorganization Plan of ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-11-25"},"text":"November 25, 2002","children":[],"tail":", as modified, set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t6/s542"},"text":"section 542 of Title 6","children":[],"tail":". For establishment of U.S. Customs and Border Protection in the Department of Homeland Security, treated as if included in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/296"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–296","children":[],"tail":" as of "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-11-25"},"text":"Nov. 25, 2002","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t6/s211"},"text":"section 211 of Title 6","children":[],"tail":", as amended generally by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/125"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–125","children":[],"tail":", and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/125/s802/b"},"text":"section 802(b) of Pub. L. 114–125","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t6/s211"},"text":"section 211 of Title 6","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
